data.title: Graduation 2008
data.meta_description:
Graduation 2008 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf) or read online for free. Shivani Faust was adopted from an orphanage run by Mother Teresa in India. She was found as an abandoned newborn with badly burned legs outside the orphanage. Beverly Faust adopted her and had surgery performed that saved her legs. Now Shivani is graduating from Roseburg High School and plans to attend college to become a nurse or midwife so she can help others around the world. 

Kristen Davis is the salutatorian at North Douglas High School. She plans to attend college and then become a teacher like both of her parents. Davis was involved in many sports in high school and learned about teamwork and leadership.
